              </row>

              <row bottom="minor">
                <cell right="minor">Distance traveled in meters, <m>D</m></cell>
                <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>
                <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>
                <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>
                <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>
                <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>
                <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>
                <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>
                <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>
              </row>
            </tabular>
          </table>
        </statement>
      </task>

      <task>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Which variable is the independent variable? Why do you think so?
          </p>
        </statement>
      </task>

    </exercise>

    <exercise xml:id="exer-tort-graph">
      <introduction>
        <p>
          Use the graph in <xref ref="fig-time-dist-tort-plot"/>. For each axis, choose a scale so the graph shows the tortoise's complete race, points are easy to plot, and you use as much of the graph as possible.
        </p>
        <figure xml:id="fig-time-dist-tort-plot">
          <caption>Plot for Graphing the Tortoise's Time and Distance</caption>
          <image source="time-dist-tort-plot" width="80%">
            <description></description>
          </image>
        </figure>
      </introduction>

      <task>
        <statement>
          <p>
            The horizontal axis represents the independent variable. Label it using the scale you chose.
          </p>
        </statement>
      </task>

      <task>
        <statement>
          <p>
            The vertical axis represents the dependent variable. Label it using your chosen scale.
          </p>
        </statement>
      </task>

      <task>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Label each axis with the variable it represents.
          </p>
        </statement>
      </task>

      <task>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Sketch a graph that represents the tortoise's progress during the race using the data in <xref ref="tbl-tort-time"/>.
          </p>
        </statement>
      </task>
    </exercise>

    <exercise xml:id="exer-tort-time-minute">
      <task>
        <statement>
          <p>
            In one minute, how far did the tortoise travel? What does this number represent in terms of the tortoise's movement during the race?
          </p>
        </statement>
      </task>

      <task>
        <statement>
          <p>
            How can you find the distance the tortoise traveled directly from the number of minutes that have elapsed since the start of the race?
          </p>
        </statement>
      </task>

      <task xml:id="exer-tort-time-eq">
        <statement>
          <p>
            Let <m>t</m> represent the elapsed time in minutes and <m>D</m> represent the distance in meters traveled by the tortoise. Write an equation showing the relationship between <m>t</m> and <m>D</m>:
            <me>
              D = <fillin/>
            </me>
             
          </p>
        </statement>
      </task>

      <task>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Replace <m>t</m> in the equation in <xref ref="exer-tort-time-eq"/> with some of the values in the table. What values did you get for <m>D</m> from the equation? Did the equation values for <m>D</m> match those in your table? Should they match?
          </p>
        </statement>
      </task>

      <task>
        <statement>
          <p>
            How does your answer to <xref ref="exer-tort-time-minute"/> relate to the equation you found in <xref ref="exer-tort-time-eq"/>?
          </p>
        </statement>
      </task>
    </exercise>

